cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for lexical relation learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves supervised learning and classification, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of pre-trained embeddings and spectral clustering suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which could be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of word embeddings and vector subtraction suggests a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
